name: Salvation Army Inglewood
review_text: Just open for the Second Sunday in a row !Was opened last week! Social distancing is being done had roughly 30 people today and still had seats left over . They Have  a good service and do a lot for the community before the pandemic more than other so-called churches being so much bigger and brag about what they're doing!! They're still passing food out on Thursdays still may be limited but they're still making an effort to do that! That's more than I can say some major churches are doing and other public nonprofits! The senior center across the street was doing a lot of other things until the pandemic they could be opening up shortly!! Will keep you informed!!
